      "content": "but i literally have manuka honey right here and i've read so many articles about how it's used in clinical settings for wound care. it's basically antiseptic, right? if the bleeding stays slow and i keep it clean with the honey, why would i really need to pay for a clinic visit? it feels like a lot of unnecessary stress/money for a cut that is starting to slow down.",
